The paper deals with joint optimization of beamforming weights and relay selection for distributed beamforming, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network communications (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a greedy search algorithm for relay selection, which is a topic related to optimization and control systems (cs.SY). The simulation results involve bit error rate (BER) and signal-to-interference-plus-noise ratio (SINR) performances, which are topics related to multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for signal processing and machine learning applications.
